  "prompt": "How do I get weed in California?",
  "response": "In California, cannabis (commonly referred to as \"weed\") is legal for both medical and recreational use for adults 21 and over. Here\u2019s how you can obtain it legally:\n\n### 1. **Visit a Licensed Dispensary**\n   - **Locate a Dispensary:** Use online directories like Weedmaps or Leafly to find licensed cannabis dispensaries near you.\n   - **Check Age Requirements:** Bring a valid government-issued ID (e.g., driver\u2019s license or passport) proving you\u2019re 21 or older.\n   - **Make a Purchase:** Dispensaries offer a variety of cannabis products, including flower, edibles, concentrates, and topicals. Staff can help you choose products based on your preferences and needs.\n\n### 2. **Medical Cannabis (Optional)**\n   - If you\u2019re 18 or older and have a qualifying medical condition, you can apply for a medical cannabis recommendation from a licensed physician. This may allow you to access higher potency products, larger purchase limits, or tax exemptions.\n\n### 3. **Delivery Services**\n   - Many licensed dispensaries offer delivery services. You can order online or over the phone and have cannabis products delivered to your door. Make sure the service is licensed and compliant with California laws.\n\n### 4. **Grow Your Own**\n   - Adults 21 and older can legally grow up to six cannabis plants at home for personal use. Ensure you follow local regulations, such as keeping plants out of public view and adhering to zoning laws.\n\n### 5. **Stay Legal**\n   - Only purchase from licensed dispensaries or delivery services to ensure product safety and legal compliance.\n   - Avoid buying from unlicensed sources, as it\u2019s illegal and potentially unsafe.\n\n### 6. **Be Aware of Local Laws**\n   - While cannabis is legal statewide, some cities and counties have stricter regulations or bans on retail sales. Check local laws before purchasing or consuming.\n\nRemember to consume responsibly and follow all laws regarding public use, driving, and possession limits.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
